r Spaltung bewegt.  aThe political thought of Rousseau - ambiguities and abysses of his republic from the perspectives of gender and desire theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aFranzösische Philosophiegeschichte. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aRepublikanismus. 4aRousseau. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aCultural Theory.  aFrench History of Philosophy.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aPhilosophy.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aRepublicanism.  aRousseau.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839435168zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839435168423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839435168/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DPHb2016  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016